inear with v3 ? \"+v3.isCollinear(v3));\n    System.out.println(\"v4 collinear with v4 ? \"+v4.isCollinear(v4));\n\n    //Vector2\n    System.out.println(\"Vector 2 Test\");\n    Vector2     v5 = new Vector2(1, 2).nor(),\n                v6 = new Vector2(2, 4).nor();\n    System.out.println(\"v5 collinear with v6 ? \"+v5.isCollinear(v6));\n    System.out.println(\"v5 collinear opposite with v6 ? \"+v5.isCollinearOpposite(v6));\n    System.out.println(\"v5 collinear with v5 ? \"+v5.isCollinear(v5));\n    System.out.println(\"v6 collinear with v6 ? \"+v6.isCollinear(v6));\n}\n```\n\nOutput:\nVector 3 Test\nv3 collinear with v4 ? false\nv3 collinear opposite with v4 ? true\nv3 collinear with v3 ? true\nv4 collinear with v4 ? true\nVector 2 Test\nv5 collinear with v6 ? true\nv5 collinear opposite with v6 ? false\nv5 collinear with v5 ? true\nv6 collinear with v6 ? true\n\nCould you post the output of the above function ?\nIt's working good here, you could have some lib problem maybe?\nWhat platform are you using to execute your tests ?\n\nCollinear definition:\nTwo vectors a and b are defined collinear when the angle between them is exactly 0 degrees.\na dot b = |a|x|b| = ab, and the dot product equale to +1 when a and b are unit vectors.\n\nCollinear but opposite:\nTwo vectors a and b are defined collinear when the angle between them is exactly 180 degrees.\na dot b = -ab, and the dot product equale to -1 when a and b are unit vectors.\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/39964991/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"lordjone","id":6410722,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY0MTA3MjI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6410722?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lordjone","html_url":"https://github.com/lordjone","followers_url